    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-22T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-22T02:00:00-05:00" n="258"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/2624: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-22T16:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1917—4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My telegram of June 18, 4 p. m.,<note n="36" xml:id="d258fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1917#pg_259">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, p. 259</ref>.</note> and
                    your telegram of June 19, 4 p. m. just received.<note n="37" xml:id="d258fn2"
                        >Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The draft which the Minister for Foreign Affairs handed me on June 18 with the
                    statement that it was a copy of the memorandum handed on June 15 to the
                    Secretary of State<note n="36" xml:id="d258fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1917#pg_259">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, p. 259</ref>.</note>
                    contains the declaration “Japan possesses paramount interests both political and
                    economic in China.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
